[SN]TITLE[SN]
Dumfries man in court on culpable homicide charge

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A 24-year-old man has made a brief appearance at Dumfries Sheriff Court on a charge of culpable homicide.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Daniel McGuire, of Dumfries, made no plea or declaration and was remanded in custody.
It followed the death of a 44-year-old man after an incident in the town 10 days ago.
Daniel Skelton, of Bellshill, died at the Western General in Edinburgh on Friday after being taken there with a head injury.
